{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_019b899THAjbbubiHthXXiCf", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "toolu_vrtx_01Ciirc3wzGqUsUAWRsYX3jx", "name": "Edit", "input": {"replace_all": false, "file_path": "/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/vector-databases.md", "old_string": "## Popular Options", "new_string": "## Key Concepts\n\n- **Embeddings** \u2014 dense numerical representations of text, images, or other content; the format vector DBs store and search\n- **Cosine similarity** \u2014 primary distance metric; measures the angle between vectors regardless of magnitude\n- **HNSW** \u2014 the ANN algorithm most vector DBs use; see [Vector Similarity Search](vector-similarity-search.md) for detail\n- **Speed vs. recall trade-off** \u2014 exact search is precise but O(n); approximate (ANN) is fast but may miss the nearest neighbor\n\n## Popular Options"}}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 2717, "cache_read_input_tokens": 37953, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 2717, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 13}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "0dd70f00-cdf8-4409-bc72-42e09c15954a", "uuid": "0bdff47c-358f-4edd-b9a4-092307d5aeef", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011CcrmJWdi1WHRG9Ryk1ATC", "timestamp": "2026-07-09T16:02:20.531Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01Ciirc3wzGqUsUAWRsYX3jx","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/vector-databases.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0dd70f00-cdf8-4409-bc72-42e09c15954a","uuid":"d4ccf01a-ade5-48e6-b791-38ac1cd6db29","timestamp":"2026-07-09T16:02:20.541Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/vector-databases.md","oldString":"## Popular Options","newString":"## Key Concepts\n\n- **Embeddings** — dense numerical representations of text, images, or other content; the format vector DBs store and search\n- **Cosine similarity** — primary distance metric; measures the angle between vectors regardless of magnitude\n- **HNSW** — the ANN algorithm most vector DBs use; see [Vector Similarity Search](vector-similarity-search.md) for detail\n- **Speed vs. recall trade-off** — exact search is precise but O(n); approximate (ANN) is fast but may miss the nearest neighbor\n\n## Popular Options","originalFile":"# Vector Databases\n\nA vector database stores data as high-dimensional vectors (embeddings) and enables fast similarity search. They are a key component in [RAG](retrieval-augmented-generation.md) pipelines, recommendation systems, and semantic search.\n\n## Popular Options\n\n- **ChromaDB** — open-source, easy to set up, Python-native\n- **Pinecone** — managed service, scales automatically\n- **Weaviate** — open-source, supports hybrid search (vector + keyword)\n- **Qdrant** — open-source, Rust-based, high performance\n- **pgvector** — PostgreSQL extension; adds vector storage and ANN search to an existing Postgres DB\n\n## How They Work\n\n1. Documents are converted to embeddings using a model\n2. Embeddings are indexed for fast nearest-neighbor search\n3. At query time, the query is embedded and compared to stored vectors\n4. The most similar vectors (and their associated documents) are returned\n\n## Use Cases\n\n- [RAG systems](retrieval-augmented-generation.md) for grounding LLM responses\n- Semantic search across large document collections\n- Recommendation engines\n- Image and audio similarity search\n\n## Related\n\n- [Vector Similarity Search](vector-similarity-search.md) — the algorithms (HNSW, IVF) that power the nearest-neighbor queries vector DBs run\n- [Retrieval-Augmented Generation](retrieval-augmented-generation.md) — primary consumer of vector DB retrieval\n\n## Sources\n\n- sources/vector-databases.md\n- Ingested: 2026-07-09 (updated: added pgvector)\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":2,"oldLines":6,"newStart":2,"newLines":13,"lines":[" "," A vector database stores data as high-dimensional vectors (embeddings) and enables fast similarity search. They are a key component in [RAG](retrieval-augmented-generation.md) pipelines, recommendation systems, and semantic search."," ","+## Key Concepts","+","+- **Embeddings** — dense numerical representations of text, images, or other content; the format vector DBs store and search","+- **Cosine similarity** — primary distance metric; measures the angle between vectors regardless of magnitude","+- **HNSW** — the ANN algorithm most vector DBs use; see [Vector Similarity Search](vector-similarity-search.md) for detail","+- **Speed vs. recall trade-off** — exact search is precise but O(n); approximate (ANN) is fast but may miss the nearest neighbor","+"," ## Popular Options"," "," - **ChromaDB** — open-source, easy to set up, Python-native"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
